{"title_page": "1899 in music", "text_new": "{{YYYY music|1899}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1899|music}}\nEvents in the year '''1899 in music'''.\n\n<!-- formerly (18apr07):\n{{yearbox|\n| in?=in music\n| cp=18th Century\n| c=19th century\n| cf=20th century\n\n| yp1=1896\n| yp2=1897\n| yp3=1898\n| year=1899\n| ya1=1900\n| ya2=1901\n| ya3=1902\n\n| dp3=1860s\n| dp2=1870s\n| dp1=1880s\n| d=1890s\n| dn1=1900s\n| dn2=1910s\n| dn3=1920s\n}}\n-->\n\n==Specific locations==\n*[[1899 in Norwegian music]]\n\n== Events ==\n*[[January 25]] \u2013 [[Adelina Patti]] marries her third husband, Baron Rolf Cederstr\u00f6m.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Edward T. James|author2=Janet Wilson James|author3=Paul S. Boyer|title=Notable American Women, 1607\u20131950: A Biographical Dictionary|url=https://books.google.com/?id=rVLOhGt1BX0C&pg=RA2-PA31|year=1971|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-62734-5|pages=31}}</ref>\n*[[March 3]] \u2013 [[Richard Strauss]] conducts the premiere of ''[[Ein Heldenleben]]'' with the Frankfurter Opern- und Museumsorchester.\n*[[April 26]]\n**[[Jean Sibelius]]'s [[Symphony No. 1 (Sibelius)|Symphony No. 1]] is premiered in [[Helsinki]].\n**Tenor [[Antonio Paoli]] makes his d\u00e9but in Rossini's ''[[William Tell (opera)|William Tell]]'' in Paris.\n*[[May 27]] \u2013 [[Maurice Ravel]] conducts the first performance of his song cycle ''[[Sh\u00e9h\u00e9razade]]''.\n*[[June 19]] \u2013 [[Edward Elgar]]'s ''[[Enigma Variations]]'' are premiered in [[London]].\n*[[September 18]] \u2013 [[Scott Joplin]]'s ''[[Maple Leaf Rag]]'' is registered for copyright as [[ragtime]] music enjoys mainstream popularity in the [[United States]].\n*[[October 19]] \u2013 [[Claude Debussy]] marries Rosalie Texier,<ref>{{cite book|author1=Fran\u00e7ois Lesure|author2=Marie Rolf|title=Claude Debussy: A Critical Biography|url=https://books.google.com/?id=c_adDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA156|year=2019|publisher=Boydell & Brewer|isbn=978-1-58046-903-6|pages=156\u2013161}}</ref> having lived for nine years with her best friend; the marriage lasts only five years.\n*[[December 30]] \u2013 [[Samuel Coleridge-Taylor]] marries Jessie Walmisley.<ref>{{cite book|author=Samuel Coleridge-Taylor|title=Symphonic variations on an African air: opus 63|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-tAeaQEFsQEC&pg=PP10|date=1 January 2007|publisher=A-R Editions, Inc.|isbn=978-0-89579-597-7|pages=viii}}</ref>\n*''date unknown''\n**Charles Hale's song \"At a Darktown Cakewalk\" includes an early appearance of the riff \"[[Shave and a Haircut]]\".<ref>{{cite book|first=James|last=Fuld|title=The Book of World-Famous Music: Classical, Popular, and Folk|edition=5th|location=New York|publisher=Dover Publications|year=2000|page=495}}</ref>\n**[[Billy Murray (singer)|Billy Murray]] makes his singing debut.\n\n==Published popular music==\n[[Image:ImpecuniousDavisMills.jpg|200px|thumb]]\n\n* \"Absent\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. [[Catherine Young Glen]] m. [[John W. Metcalf]]\n* \"Always!\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Charles Horwitz m. Frederick V. Bowers\n* \"Cake Walk In The Sky\" by [[Ben Harney]]\n* \"Come Home [[George Dewey|Dewey]] We Won't Do A Thing To You\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w.m. [[Paul Dresser]]\n* \"A Coon Band Contest\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;m. [[Arthur Pryor]]\n* \"Cotton Pickers Rag & Cakewalk\" by William Braun\n* \"Doan Ye Cry, Mah Honey\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w.m. Alfred W. Noll\n* \"[[Hands Across the Sea (march)|Hands Across The Sea]]\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;m. [[John Philip Sousa]]\n* \"[[Hearts And Flowers]]\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Mary D. Brine m. [[Theodore Moses Tobani]]\n* \"[[Hello! Ma Baby]]\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w.m. Ida Emerson & [[Joseph E. Howard]]\n* \"I'd Leave My Happy Home For You\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Will A. Heelan m. [[Harry Von Tilzer]]\n* \"If Only You Were Mine\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Harry B. Smith m. [[Victor Herbert]]\n* \"I'll Be Your Sweetheart\" w.m. [[Harry Dacre]]\n* \"