l Coleridge-Taylor|title=Symphonic variations on an African air: opus 63|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-tAeaQEFsQEC&pg=PP10|date=1 January 2007|publisher=A-R Editions, Inc.|isbn=978-0-89579-597-7|pages=viii}}</ref>\n*''date unknown''\n**Charles Hale's song \"At a Darktown Cakewalk\" includes an early appearance of the riff \"[[Shave and a Haircut]]\".<ref>{{cite book|first=James|last=Fuld|title=The Book of World-Famous Music: Classical, Popular, and Folk|edition=5th|location=New York|publisher=Dover Publications|year=2000|page=495}}</ref>\n**[[Billy Murray (singer)|Billy Murray]] makes his singing debut.\n\n==Published popular music==\n[[Image:ImpecuniousDavisMills.jpg|200px|thumb]]\n\n* \"Absent\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. [[Catherine Young Glen]] m. [[John W. Metcalf]]\n* \"Always!\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Charles Horwitz m. Frederick V. Bowers\n* \"Cake Walk In The Sky\" by [[Ben Harney]]\n* \"Come Home [[George Dewey|Dewey]] We Won't Do A Thing To You\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w.m. [[Paul Dresser]]\n* \"A Coon Band Contest\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;m. [[Arthur Pryor]]\n* \"Cotton Pickers Rag & Cakewalk\" by William Braun\n* \"Doan Ye Cry, Mah Honey\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w.m. Alfred W. Noll\n* \"[[Hands Across the Sea (march)|Hands Across The Sea]]\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;m. [[John Philip Sousa]]\n* \"[[Hearts And Flowers]]\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Mary D. Brine m. [[Theodore Moses Tobani]]\n* \"[[Hello! Ma Baby]]\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w.m. Ida Emerson & [[Joseph E. Howard]]\n* \"I'd Leave My Happy Home For You\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Will A. Heelan m. [[Harry Von Tilzer]]\n* \"If Only You Were Mine\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;w. Harry B. Smith m. [[Victor Herbert]]\n* \"I'll Be Your Sweetheart\" w.m. [[Harry Dacre]]\n* \"Impecunious Davis\" by [[Kerry Mills]]\n* \"[[Keep on the Sunny Side]]\", w. A. Blenkhorn, m. J.H. Entwisle\n* \"Mandy Lee\" w.m. Thurland Chattaway\n* \"[[Maple Leaf Rag